ANDIO — Accessible Name and Description Inspector Offline
Copyright 2026 Blueprint Technologies

This product is a derivative work based on ANDI (Accessible Name and
Description Inspector), originally developed by the Social Security
Administration (SSA), Accessible Solutions Branch.

Original work: https://github.com/SSAgov/ANDI
Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0

ANDIO ports ANDI's accessibility check logic from browser-based JavaScript
to a static Python scanner for CI/CD integration. The check rules, alert
definitions, and WCAG mappings are derived from ANDI's source code. ANDIO
does not contain any original ANDI source code — the implementation is an
independent rewrite in Python using BeautifulSoup for HTML parsing.
